This paper deals with probabilistic reasoning, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of qualitative probabilities, which is a topic in uncertainty reasoning and decision making (cs.SI). The experimental comparison of different probabilistic reasoning methods involves data analysis and statistical inference, which are topics in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the practical application of probabilistic reasoning to machine diagnosis, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
